<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10564&amp;p=119132#p119132</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10564&amp;p=119132#p119132"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Megaman X2 on Rockman X3 PCB]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10564&amp;p=119132#p119132"><![CDATA[
RMX2/MMX2 uses 2x8Mbit ROM chips, RMX3/MMX3 uses 1x16Mbit ROM.  Here's what byuu told me about running RMX2 on an RMX3 board<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />And by the way, if you do attempt to flash in RMX2, it will need one tiny code patch. Somewhere in the game it writes #$01 to $7f52. That needs to be commented out or set to #$00. (I may have the bit flipped in my head again.) The register toggles whether banks 20-3f go to the second ROM chip or not. Which obviously there will only be one.<br /></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5348">qwertymodo</a> — Tue Oct 08, 2013 10:00 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
